British prime minister David Cameron allowed his former spokesman Andy Coulson, the ex-editor of the now-defunct News of the World tabloid, access to some of the British government's most sensitive secrets without full security clearance, the Leveson Inquiry is told. (Al Jazeera) (The Guardian)Supreme Leader of Iran Ali Khamenei calls nuclear weapons and their use "an unforgivable sin" and defends Iran's right to use nuclear energy for medical and peaceful purposes. (CNN)